race.comment: BRITISH GEM (11) needed the run at Newcastle first-up and then showed more like her best, beaten 1.6L at Doomben. Fitter again and will enjoy a drop in class. She's ready to find the winners' list. MISS HIGHFALUTIN (17) is in the premier stable and also presents third-up. Has been well supported in both stats this preparation, with the latest at Doomben. Has a 2kg claim, and the winkers are on for the first time. Should be ready to fire. MY CHARM (14) is a lightly raced improver in the Waller yard. Brings a decent effort from Doomben and maps for the run of the race. She won't have to improve much to feature. SLIPSAIN (2) surprised racing forward at Doomben first-up and gave it away late, beaten 1.8L. He has more to give and will likely be restrained today from a wide gate. Fitter he can make the finish with luck in the run.
